<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20556] Unprepared batches unnecessarily measure prepared statement size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20556</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running a performance regression test recently, we noticed that unprepared batches still call &lt;tt&gt;QueryProcessor.measurePstmnt()&lt;/tt&gt;. This is unnecessary of course, but wouldn&apos;t have been noticeable if it wasn&apos;t also accounting for about 8% of allocations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
